The paper deals with the problem of modifying a graph to satisfy certain degree constraints, which is a classic problem in graph theory and combinatorics. The use of operations such as edge addition, deletion, and vertex deletion suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The problem of modifying a graph to satisfy degree constraints is also related to the study of graph connectivity and graph theory, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) categories.
